user_id,image_paths,user_claim,claim_object,evidence_standard_met,evidence_standard_met_reason,risk_flags,issue_type,object_part,claim_status,claim_status_justification,supporting_image_ids,valid_image,severity
user_002,images/test/case_001/img_1.jpg;images/test/case_001/img_2.jpg;images/test/case_001/img_3.jpg,"Customer: Morning. I parked near office and later noticed something off in the front. | Agent: Is this about one part or multiple parts? | Customer: Two things, I think. The front bumper looks damaged and the left headlight also looks affected. | Agent: Should we review both as part of this claim? | Customer: Yes, front bumper and left headlight together.",car,false,"The images do not provide a clear view of the front bumper to assess the claimed dent. Image 'img_1' shows the front of the car but does not focus on the bumper. Image 'img_2' shows a scratch on the side of the car, not a dent on the front bumper. Image 'img_3' shows a close-up of the headlight, which is not relevant to the claim of a dent on the front bumper.",damage_not_visible;non_original_image;manual_review_required,dent,front_bumper,not_enough_information,"The front bumper is not clearly visible in any of the images provided. Image 'img_1' shows the front of the car but does not focus on the bumper. Image 'img_2' shows a scratch on the side of the car, not a dent on the front bumper. Image 'img_3' shows a close-up of the headlight, which is not relevant to the claim of a dent on the front bumper. Image quality issues and lack of relevant images prevent a clear assessment of the claimed damage.",none,false,unknown
user_005,images/test/case_003/img_1.jpg,"Customer: Need to file a car damage claim. | Agent: What part of the car? | Customer: Door. | Agent: Scratch, dent, or paint issue? | Customer: A deep dent on the door panel. It was not there before.",car,true,"The image (img_1) clearly shows the door panel from an angle where surface marks or deformation can be assessed, and no dent is visible. The image quality is good with no flags indicating issues.",damage_not_visible;user_history_risk;manual_review_required,dent,door,contradicted,"img_1 shows a clear view of the door panel with no visible dent. The image quality is good, and the damage assessor confirmed no damage was present. Given the user's history of exaggerated claims, this context is noted but does not change the assessment.",img_1,true,none
user_004,images/test/case_010/img_1.jpg;images/test/case_010/img_2.jpg;images/test/case_010/img_3.jpg,"Customer: I have two car issues in the same incident. | Support: Please list them separately. | Customer: First, the door is dented. Second, the rear bumper is damaged. | Support: Should both be verified from these images? | Customer: Yes, both parts are included.",car,true,"img_1 clearly shows a dent on the door of the car, meeting the evidence standard for assessing the claimed damage.",none,dent,door,supported,"img_1 shows a clear dent on the door, supporting the claim. The images meet the evidence standard, and there are no image quality issues affecting the assessment.",img_1,true,medium
user_007,images/test/case_005/img_1.jpg;images/test/case_005/img_2.jpg,"Customer: Hi, I am not sure which photo is clearest, but my side mirror is the issue. | Support: What happened to it? | Customer: It seems missing or broken after the car was parked outside. | Support: Should we ignore unrelated car photos if any? | Customer: Please focus on the side mirror claim.",car,false,"The submitted images do not provide a clear view of the side mirror to evaluate the claim of a missing part. The images are clear and show a car, but the side mirror is not visible, making it impossible to confirm the claim.",damage_not_visible,missing_part,side_mirror,not_enough_information,"The side mirror is not clearly visible in the provided images to assess the claimed missing part. Therefore, there is not enough information to determine the validity of the claim.",none,true,none
user_008,images/test/case_006/img_1.jpg,"Customer: Hi, I am not sure if I am filing this in the right place, so please bear with me for a minute. | Support: No problem, tell me what happened. | Customer: The weather was bad last night and I had parked outside because the covered parking was full. In the morning I was already late, so I did not inspect the car properly. | Support: When did you first notice a possible issue? | Customer: Later in the day, after a colleague mentioned that my car looked a little different from the front. I walked around it twice and honestly could not decide if I was overthinking it. | Support: Which area should we review? | Customer: I first checked the windshield and the sides, but those are not what I want to claim. | Support: Okay, what is the actual damage claim? | Customer: The hood seems to have small hail dents, so please review the hood for hail damage.",car,false,"The image (img_1) is too blurry to assess the presence of small hail dents on the hood, and it appears to be a non-original stock photo with a watermark. Therefore, the evidence standard was not met.",blurry_image;damage_not_visible;non_original_image;user_history_risk;manual_review_required,dent,hood,not_enough_information,"img_1 shows small hail dents on the hood, but the image is too blurry and non-original to confirm the damage. Given the user history context and past claims requiring image-quality review, there is a risk of potential misinterpretation, but the claim status remains 'not enough information' due to insufficient visual evidence.",img_1,false,unknown
